vectorData.altText: 7. Identify the layer indicated by the letter A. Be specific.

aka s. germinativum
Rapid basal cell cycling gives rise to daughter cells that either stay behind as stem cells or migrate superficially.
Proteins called keratins are produced on free ribosomes and start to accumulate in the cytoplasm. Keratins assemble into keratin intermediate filaments, which form:
hemidesmosomes, connecting the basal cells to the underlying BM
desmosomes, connecting adjacent basal cells, and basal cells to the overlying keratinocytes of the s. spinosum
These connections give skin its mechanical strength.
Account for the overwhelming majority of skin cancers.  This type of carcinoma grows slowly and rarely metastasize. Etiology can be due to damage caused by UV radiation.
That's right! Stratum basale is the innermost layer of the epidermis. Keratinocytes in this layer undergo rapid cell cycling to maintain skin thickness.
